byline.original: By ERIC LICHTBLAU and STEVEN LEE MYERS

abstract: Federal Bureau of Investigation releases 100 pages of internal files regarding inquiry into Hillary Clinton's use of email during her time as secretary of state that put spotlight on senior State Dept official Patrick F Kennedy; documents show Kennedy was involved with dispute with FBI over security classification of some of Clinton's emails, and raise possibility that deal was struck between Kennedy and FBI official; State Dept and FBI deny any such discussion or agreement.
lead_paragraph: Newly released documents include discussion of a possible “quid pro quo” to settle a dispute between the State Department and the F.B.I. over the classification of one of Mrs. Clinton’s emails.
snippet: Newly released documents include discussion of a possible “quid pro quo” to settle a dispute between the State Department and the F.B.I. over the classification of one of Mrs. Clinton’s emails....

headline.main: Agencies Clashed on Classification of Clinton Email, Inquiry Shows
headline.print_headline: Agencies Split on Classifying Clinton Emails
